# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# Type can be:
#   feat     - A new feature
#   fix      - A bug fix
#   docs     - Documentation only changes
#   style    - Changes that do not affect the meaning of the code
#   refactor - A code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#   perf     - A code change that improves performance
#   test     - Adding missing tests or correcting existing tests
#   chore    - Changes to the build process or auxiliary tools
#   ci       - Changes to CI configuration files and scripts
#   build    - Changes that affect the build system or external dependencies
#
# Scope can be:
#   core     - Core modules (utils, event-bus, api-client, etc.)
#   app      - Application modules (chat, knowledge, cae, etc.)
#   ui       - UI components (particles, mascot, etc.)
#   services - Service modules (ai-service, config-service)
#   css      - Stylesheets
#   html     - HTML templates
#   build    - Build scripts and configuration
#   deps     - Dependencies
#
# Subject should be:
#   - Imperative mood (add, fix, update, not added, fixed, updated)
#   - Not capitalized
#   - No period at the end
#   - Maximum 50 characters
#
# Body (optional):
#   - Explain what and why, not how
#   - Wrap at 72 characters
#   - Use bullet points for multiple changes
#
# Footer (optional):
#   - Reference issues: Fixes #123, Closes #456
#   - Breaking changes: BREAKING CHANGE: description
#
# Examples:
#   feat(chat): add message typing indicator
#   fix(ui): resolve particle animation stutter
#   perf(core): optimize event delegation
#   docs(readme): update installation instructions
#   refactor(utils): simplify debounce implementation
#   style(css): format with prettier
#   test(chat): add unit tests for message parser
#   chore(build): update eslint configuration
#   deps: upgrade eslint to v8
#
